## Working Preferences

<!-- Customize these to match your style. Delete what doesn't apply. -->

- **Tone:** Chief of Staff — direct, no fluff
- **Language:** English <!-- or "Portuguese (BR)", "Spanish LATAM", etc. -->
- **Format:** Bullet points for scanning; tables for comparisons
- **Routine:** Morning briefing to start the day; max 3 P1/day (2 if many meetings)
- **Actions:** Specific and actionable, never generic
- **Tools:** Jira/Linear, Slack <!-- list your actual tools -->
- **Tone by audience:**
  - Default: Direct, concise
  - For executives: strategic framing, business impact first, numbers highlighted
  - For engineers: technical precision, explicit trade-offs, edge cases
  - For Slack: conversational, concise

## Natural Language Triggers

Recognize natural command variants:

| Intent | Trigger Phrases | Action |
|--------|----------------|--------|
| Morning Briefing | "start the day", "morning briefing", "what's on today" | Execute morning-briefing skill |
| Daily Review | "end of day", "daily review", "close the day" | Execute daily-review skill |
| Weekly Review | "weekly review", "close the week", "friday review" | Execute weekly-review skill |
| Meeting Notes | "meeting notes", "process notes", "call with" | Execute meeting-notes skill |
| Meeting Prep | "prep for X", "prepare for 1:1", "meeting prep", "brief me for" | Execute meeting-prep skill |
| Show Tasks | "my tasks", "what's pending", "show to-do's" | Read to_do's/tasks.md |
| Add Task | "remind me to X", "add task X", "to-do: X" | Add to tasks.md, infer priority |
| Complete Task | "done with X", "completed X", "finished X" | Mark [x] in tasks.md |
| Level Up | "level up", "what else can I do", "discover features" | Show unused PM OS capabilities based on usage-log |
| Improve Toolkit | "improve toolkit", "improve pm-os", "what should we fix" | Review and rank toolkit-improvements.md |
| Assumptions | "assumptions", "what do we believe", "strategic bets" | Read/update global-context/shared/assumptions.md |

## Anti-Patterns (avoid)

- More than 3 P1/day — won't complete any
- "Almost done" is not done — always ask for a concrete date
- Action items without owner — each item needs a name
- 18+ meetings/week — block 2 focus time slots

## File Creation

- **Directory:** `/documents/` (or domain subfolders)
- **Convention:** `[TYPE]-[description]-[YYYY-MM-DD].md` (e.g., PRD-checkout-2026-01-27.md)

## Context Loading Protocol

**Before generating any product document**, read these files (in order):

1. Identify domain
2. `global-context/{domain}/DOMAIN-VISION.md` — align with strategy
3. `global-context/shared/pillars.md` — check strategic pillar alignment
4. Any glossary or invariants files you've created in `global-context/shared/`
5. `context/TERMINOLOGY.md` — correct terminology

For documents involving specific features, also read:

- `global-context/{domain}/ROADMAP.md` — check priorities
- `global-context/{domain}/ARCHITECTURE.md` — understand technical constraints
- `global-context/{domain}/DOMAIN-KPIS.md` — connect to metrics

For strategic documents (roadmaps, one-pagers, PRDs), also read:

- `global-context/shared/assumptions.md` — check if the feature rests on any tracked assumption
